{
  "stem": "3820.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In leaving for the forest, my Uncle Chaim took us out at night through a part that they had-- they had cut and camouflaged the wires, because the ghetto was-- was surrounded by barbed wire, with one gate in and out.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- the-- the area, as I said, had many forests.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember the forests more clearly than anything else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And through a partition there that they had made-- that he had made over the weeks or so that he had been accomplishing this-- we-- my mother and father and my grandfather and I were the-- he took us out first.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he took us to an area in the forest that he had made ready.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember the leaves were gold, and the trees were so tall.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Then about a week later, he brought his younger sister, my Aunt Chava, and my Uncle Sana into the forest.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was another family there whom I don't remember at all.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But this little group lived there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We-- strange, I don't remember what we ate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I-- I don't remember any of the food, but we must have had something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know where it came from.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Germans were becoming more and more active.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The patrols through the areas were almost on a nightly basis, and we would go into our underground shelter.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when my Uncle Chaim, who was always on the move-- they had a signal that it was him when he came during the day, so that we-- we opened this little square opening.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there were times when we came out in the daylight when it was quiet.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
